<h1>Caesar cipher demo</h1>
<p>To encrypt a message, enter the message in the <strong>Plaintext</strong=
> textbox, specify the shift, and click <strong>Encrypt</strong>. To decryp=
t a message, enter the message in the <strong>Ciphertext</strong> textbox, =
specify the shift, and click <strong>Decrypt</strong>. Note that, in this i=
mplementation, strings are converted to upper case before encryption/decryp=
tion, and spaces and punctuation marks are not encrypted/decrypted. </p>
<form action=3D"https://csis.gmu.edu/albanese/labs/caesar_cypher.php" metho=
d=3D"post" name=3D"caesar" id=3D"caesar">
  Plaintext=20
  <input name=3D"plaintext" type=3D"text" id=3D"plaintext" size=3D"30" valu=
e=3D"">=20
  <input name=3D"Command" type=3D"submit" id=3D"Command" value=3D"Encrypt">
  Shift=20
  <input name=3D"shift" type=3D"text" id=3D"shift" value=3D"4" size=3D"5">=
=20
  <input name=3D"Command" type=3D"submit" id=3D"Command" value=3D"Decrypt">
  Ciphertext
  <input name=3D"ciphertext" type=3D"text" id=3D"ciphertext" size=3D"30" va=
lue=3D"">
</form>
<p>Using this tool try to decrypt the following message: <strong>SDQMF VAN,=
 KAG NDAWQ FTQ OAPQ!</strong> </p>
